pic forcing. {In the case of anisotropic forcing,\nwhence the energy} goes from the 2D to the 3D modes at low wavenumbers,\nlarge-scale shear is created resulting in another time scale $\\tau_{sh}$,\nassociated with shear, {thereby producing} a $\\sim k^{-1}$ spectrum for the\n{total energy} with the 2D modes still following a {$\\sim k_{\\perp}^{-5/3}$}\nscaling.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 22 Mar 2012 21:24:52 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 5 Apr 2012 22:00:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-04"}
